-- Technology tree data (2026-07 leveled rework). Each entry is one NODE in the HOI4-style tree.
--
-- Schema (see .claude/plans/technology-tree-design.md and Shared/TechDomains for the modifier keys):
--   id            string  (== table key)
--   name          string  (display)
--   tab           string  (left-rail pillar: infantry/armor/artillery/naval/economy/political/command/research)
--   category      string  (sub-group / row band within the tab)
--   era           number? (era of level 1; drives left->right layout + starting distribution. nil = prereq-gated modern)
--   eraByLevel    {number}? (per-level era override; defaults to `era` for every level)
--   prerequisites {techId} (DAG edges -> the UI auto-draws connector lines from each prereq)
--   icon          string? (Icons.Ids key; UI falls back to a tab icon)
--   banner        string? (image id for the chip banner; bare number or rbxassetid://. Absent -> generative banner)
--   maxLevel      number  (1 = one-shot; >1 = leveled upgrade)
--   cost          {number} of length maxLevel  OR { base=number, growth=number }
--   starting      bool    (level 1 seeded free at start; raise with startingLevel)
--   startingLevel number? (levels granted at seed regardless of era)
--   description   string  (node detail panel)
--   effects       { [level] = { summary, modifiers = {[domainKey]=number}, unlocks = {id}, slots = number } }
--   gates         {techId} (boolean flag ids also set true on completion; leader/doctrine researchGate compat)
--
-- Buffs are MULTIPLICATIVE and hard-capped per branch (TechDomains): combat per-unit-class at 3x
-- (artillery sub-stats 2x), the additive economy/political fractions at their per-branch caps.

